From: csoliver <source@olio.ovh>
Subject: Case insensitivity in git, hub, lists and todo

This patch series includes fixes in 4 of the sourcehut repositories.

git.sr.ht:  
Made the check when creating or renaming a repository case-insensitive.
Included a commented out codeblock for checking artifacts, as I don't
know if it should apply there.  

hub.sr.ht:
Made the check case insensitive here on projects too, and also added the validation
of renames too, as it was missing.

lists.sr.ht:
Similar to git, but only on creation of mailing lists

todo.sr.ht:
Same as git, on creation and renaming of trackers and labels

I haven't included checks about if the conflicting entry is itself, because the
original doesn't have it either, but I think it might be worth doing sometime.

Partially fixes: https://todo.sr.ht/~sircmpwn/sourcehut/98
